column5: I stay at Brownlees
I like to leave on the second Saturday following ice out. So I am going to guess May 16 or exactly 100 days from today.
102 till departure an 104 till we are fishing in Nakina. I,m 3/4th packed now and can be all ready and at the door in an hour an a half......but I,m not trying to rush things!
104 days until departure. We are going into camp on Friday so we will be using all 8 days of 8 day permits. It can't come too soon!
zero days for me cause I live on Lake of The Woods but 100 or so till ice out! For some reason I am looking forward to this coming summer more than I ever have.
21......weeks that is.
124 and a wakeup for the first trip and 154 and a wakeup for the second.
Love my countdown clock. I phone and pad.
You going to Pakuni Lodge?
154 days till Witch Bay
Days til I'm back in Canada..............Not that I'm counting. How many for you guys?
I counted 135. Then I remembered the countdown site:http://www.timeanddate.com/countdown...ake+St.+Joseph
I'm at 107 too!
where ya headed? Pakwash for me. Near ear falls.
100 days to we travel and fish the opener in 101. B-
105 boating into Rainy again.
198 to northern ON for numbers, 70 to southern ON and the pigs.
195 days, 11 hours, 18 minutes and 10 seconds.

Manotak Lodge on Perrault Lake for us. I may well see you on the road! Wave as you go by. We will drive up on Friday to Nestor Falls then on to Perrault Falls on Saturday morning. I much prefer driving Hwy. 71 than Hwy. 502. It only adds about 20 minutes to the trip and it's really a lot more relaxing drive. We will fish in Nestor Falls on Friday evening and should be checked in and on Perrault Lake by 3:00 on Saturday. Can't wait! This will be my 6th trip since September of 2012.
98 days to departure
